title: Woman found dead in tub at Far North Side hotel
text:
More Articles By Dean Narciso The Columbus Dispatch • Friday September 25, 2015 11:56 PM 
Columbus police and fire officials are investigating the death – a possible drowning – of a woman at a Far North Side hotel on Friday evening. The report of a drowning came in just before 11 p.m. at the Extended Stay America hotel, 7465 High Cross Blvd., which is just north of Worthington off Rt. 23 and north of the Outerbelt. Police Sgt. Aaron Ward confirmed that a woman had been found dead in a bathtub in one of the hotel’s second-floor rooms. But it’s not yet clear whether she drowned or died some other way. Ward couldn’t say who found her or how long she’d been in the room. The victim’s name also hasn’t yet been released. An autopsy is expected to be performed by the Franklin County coroner’s office on Saturday.
